title: Highest temperatures yet to come in Europe as tourists left stranded outside Greek landmark
description: Europe is set to reach even higher temperatures over the weekend, as the Cerberus heatwave continues to grip the south of the continent.

title: Johnson calls for NATO timetable for Ukraine to join alliance
description: Boris Johnson has called for NATO to set out a clear timetable for Ukraine to join the alliance - and claimed some member nations still want to negotiate a peace deal with Vladimir Putin.

title: Women's World Cup warm-up match abandoned after 20 minutes for 'overly physical' challenges
description: A Women's World Cup warm-up match between the Republic of Ireland and Colombia was called off after just 20 minutes for "overly physical" challenges.

title: Modi's Bastille Day red carpet treatment sparks controversy - in shadow of French riots
description: French President Emmanuel Macron gave Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi - his guest of honour at the Bastille Day celebrations in Paris - the red carpet treatment, as the two countries sealed high-profile defence deals.

title: India launches space mission to far side of the moon
description: India has launched a spacecraft to the far side of the moon four years after a failed effort to land a rover softly on the lunar surface.

title: Ukraine conducts 'special operation' using speed boats and drones on Dnipro island
description: Ukrainian forces say they have conducted a "special operation" on a Dnipro island, as dramatic footage shows soldiers using speed boats and drones.

title: Bookshop fined over British graphic novel under controversial LGBT+ law
description: A bookshop in Hungary has been handed a hefty fine under the country's controversial LGBT+ literature law after selling a British graphic novel without first wrapping it in closed packaging.

title: Nursery teacher executed for poisoning childrens' porridge
description: A nursery teacher in China has been executed after killing one child and injuring 24 others by poisoning their porridge.

title: LA police chief criticises officer who punched woman twice while holding baby
description: The Los Angeles County sheriff has said an incident where a police officer punched a woman twice in the face while she held her three-week-old baby was "completely unacceptable".

title: Mystery over three 'mummified' bodies found in Rocky Mountains
description: Three "mummified" bodies have been discovered in a remote campsite in the Rocky Mountains, police have said.

title: Andrew Tate sues woman who accused him of human trafficking
description: Controversial influencer Andrew Tate is suing a Florida woman, saying she lied when she accused him of human trafficking.

title: Nearly 300 migrant children have died or disappeared this year in Mediterranean crossings
description: At least 289 children have died or disappeared attempting the dangerous Mediterranean Sea crossing from North Africa to Europe so far this year, according to UNICEF.

title: Fire kills 'nearly all' animals at wildlife centre
description: A fire has killed "nearly all" of the animals at a wildlife centre in Florida, according to its "devastated" staff.

title: Hollywood will grind to a complete halt as actors and writers both strike - it could last for months
description: Writers have been treading the pavements with picket signs outside the Netflix building in Hollywood for two months now.

title: Court clears man of groping 'because it lasted for seconds' - sparking protests on TikTok
description: An Italian court's decision to clear a janitor who groped a schoolgirl because he did it for "just a few seconds" has sparked outrage.

title: Almost two-thirds of Tinder's users are already in a relationship - and half don't even want a date
description: Nearly two-thirds of people who use Tinder are already in a relationship - with almost half of users not actually interested in finding dates, according to a new study.
